y stronger in well\nmixed substrates composed of CO2 and H2O ice, consistent with regolith-mixed\nCO2 ice grains formed by radiolysis. Additionally, we detected a 2.35-micron\nfeature in some low sub-observer latitude spectra, which might result from CO\nformed as part of a CO2 radiolytic production cycle.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 28 Nov 2021 19:44:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-11-30"}
