{"id":"2111.14333","submitter":"Alexey Rastegin","authors":"Alexey E. Rastegin, Anzhelika M. Shemet","title":"Quantum search degeneration under amplitude noise in queries to the\n  oracle","comments":"11 pages, two figures. Except for the style, v3 matches the journal\n  version. arXiv admin note: text overlap with arXiv:1708.09060","journal-ref":"Quantum Information Processing, Vol. 21, 158 (2022)","doi":"10.1007/s11128-022-03501-0","report-no":null,"categories":"quant-ph","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We examine how amplitude noise in queries to the oracle degrades a\nperformance of quantum search algorithm. The Grover search and similar\ntechniques are widely used in various quantum algorithms, including cases where\nrival parties are fighting over confidential data. Hence, the oracle-box wires\nbecome the subject of competing activity with an alteration of their normal\nfunctioning. Of course, many kinds of errors could arise in this way. Possible\ninfluence of dephasing on quantum search was already addressed in the\nliterature. Amplitude damping is another type of errors that should be analyzed\nfirst. To study the problem, we introduce a simple model of collective\ndistortions with the use of amplitude damping channel. All the quantities of\ninterest should be considered as functions of the number of Grover's\niterations. In particular, we investigate the success probability with respect\nto the parameter that characterizes the level of amplitude errors. The success\nprobability degrades significantly even if the error amount is not essential.\nNamely, this probability soon enough reduces to a value close to one half. We\nalso study trade-off relations between quantum coherence and the success\nprobability in the presence of amplitude noise.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 29 Nov 2021 05:38:52 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 10 Mar 2022 10:08:17 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 25 May 2